  "text": "The Fetch API WebIDL interface definitions and their corresponding C++ binding implementations are distributed across multiple directories in the mozilla-firefox/firefox repository.\n\nRequest Interface: The Request WebIDL interface is defined in dom/webidl/Request.webidl and implements the Fetch API Request class specification. The C++ binding implementation is located in dom/fetch/Request.h (header) and dom/fetch/Request.cpp (implementation).\n\nResponse Interface: The Response WebIDL interface is defined in dom/webidl/Response.webidl and implements the Fetch API Response class specification. The C++ binding implementation is located in dom/fetch/Response.h (header) and dom/fetch/Response.cpp (implementation).\n\nHeaders Interface: The Headers WebIDL interface is defined in dom/webidl/Headers.webidl and implements the Fetch API Headers class specification. The C++ binding implementation is located in dom/fetch/Headers.h (header) and dom/fetch/Headers.cpp (implementation).\n\nFetchEvent Interface: The FetchEvent WebIDL interface is defined in dom/webidl/FetchEvent.webidl. Unlike Request, Response, and Headers which are implemented in the dom/fetch/ directory, FetchEvent (which extends ExtendableEvent and is specific to Service Workers) has its C++ binding implementation in dom/serviceworkers/ServiceWorkerEvents.h (header) and dom/serviceworkers/ServiceWorkerEvents.cpp (implementation).\n\nSupporting Types: The Fetch.webidl file (dom/webidl/Fetch.webidl) defines the Body interface mixin and helper types used by Request and Response, such as BodyInit and the various Promise-based methods for reading body content (arrayBuffer(), blob(), json(), text(), formData(), and bytes())."
}

